thread.title: Los Fresnos looks impressive in dominating win over San Benito
thread.title_full: Los Fresnos looks impressive in dominating win over San Benito

author: DAVE FAVILA, Staff Writer
title: Los Fresnos looks impressive in dominating win over San Benito
text:
SAN BENITO — The Los Fresnos Lady Falcons showed once again why they are the premier team in District 32-6A as they rolled to a 25-5, 25-18, 25-11 win over San Benito on Saturday at the Lady Greyhounds’ gym. 
With the victory, the Lady Falcons improved to 32-8 and stayed perfect in district play at 9-0. 
Los Fresnos coach Becky Woods admitted after the match that keeping her team focused after such dominating wins is difficult. 
“It’s extremely hard,” she said. “We work hard at practice, and I tell them that when they come out: They have to play at the highest level they can because that’s what it’s going to take when we hit the playoffs. 
“We can’t let up no matter who we play because I think it’s important that we finish the district schedule undefeated in order to give us that winning edge heading into the postseason. But we can’t really look that far ahead yet. We still have games left to play and we’ll take them one at a time, playing hard all the way.” 
Despite the loss, their second in a row, the Lady Greyhounds (8-13, 4-5) remain in playoff contention and coach Ruby Medina said she wanted to make sure her team remained upbeat. 
“They just have to keep on working hard, and due to whatever happened we can’t focus on that because we have to keep on playing as a team and play as hard as they can go,” she said.
